            <note type="Gloss">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000023-2"><term type="literal_translation">literally: "added center construction" (Kroll 2015, 189-90, 507, 585);</term> <term ref="/keyword/k000172">huagong</term> which supports bracket-arms running both parallel (e.g. guazigong) and perpendicular (e.g. <term ref="/keyword/k000172">huagong</term>, <term ref="/keyword/k000103">ang</term>) to the building plane (Chen 2010, 257); also crisscross center or projection (Guo 2002, 50); "crisscross-heart"  (Zuo 2019, 175).</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000023-3">鋪作跳頭上用橫栱、昂的做法。（陳 2010, 257）。</p>   
            </note> 
